## Blog Post Typography

Blog posts use `.post-content` class which provides:

- **Body text**: Serif (Fraunces) for elevated editorial feel
- **Headings**: Serif, bold, with tight tracking
- **Blockquotes**: Serif, left-bordered with brand color
- **Lists**: Properly styled with colored markers (brand-500)
- **Links**: Brand color with underline decoration
- **Code**: Monospace with subtle background

### Markdown Element Support

All standard markdown elements are styled:

| Element | Treatment |
|---------|-----------|
| `# ## ###` | Serif headings with brand accents |
| `**bold**` | Darker weight, brand-tinted |
| `*italic*` | Same font, subtle color shift |
| `> quote` | Serif, left-bordered pull quote |
| `- bullet` | Brand-colored disc markers |
| `1. number` | Mono-styled brand markers |
| `` `code` `` | Mono with subtle bg |
| `---` | Gradient fade horizontal rule |
| `[link]()` | Brand color, underlined |

### Progressive Text Fade

For the Sagan quote, use CSS custom property `--paragraph-index` with `color-mix()`:

```css
.sagan-paragraph {
  color: color-mix(
    in oklch,
    var(--color-stone-100) calc(100% - var(--paragraph-index) * 18%),
    var(--color-stone-500) calc(var(--paragraph-index) * 18%)
  );
}
```
